The paper deals with the problem of extracting random bits from stochastic processes, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of dealing with imperfect sources of randomness, which is a problem that is relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and control systems (cs.SY).
